title: For Sale:  EXTREMELY RARE Smith & Wesson 1013 10mm Compact (4013 conversion) 4 Mags S&W  Case
postcontent: After searching for one of these 10mm conversions for years, I must sell my prize Smith & Wesson 1013 to pay medical bills. It was a 4013 with a single stack 40S&W 8 round magazine mfg. 12/30/1992 and is in pristine condition.  The forums say these were originally designed as a 10mm but when the ever popular 40 cal. 40S&W cartridge was introduced S&W decided to put a spacer in the mags for the shorter 40 cal. round and make it a compact 40S&W. Since the 10mm round is also 40 cal. just springs and barrel cartridge depth are all they had to change. This pistol barrel was reamed for the longer 10mm cartridge and frame bored out to accept a wider guide rod for a single heavy duty sping set-up. No buffer necessary. The spacer spot welds were cut out of the 4 included mags and 10mm mag followers put in.The 1013 provides maximum firepower in a compact semi-auto and with the resurgence of the 10mm cartridge they are highly sought by collectors in this condition and extremely rare since only conversions are available. This is the ultimate carry gun but I enjoy it at the range since this one was put together by an experienced converter and the spring set-up makes felt recoil the same or less than a 40 with standard 1100 to 1200 fps 10mm loads. The Hogue Grips help there as well and accuracy with the Novak Lo-Mount 3 white dot sights is every bit as good as any of my 3.5" barrel S&W 3rd Gen compacts. The 10mm fireball is simply awesome! The action is called Traditional Double Action (TDA) which describes a longer 1st shot trigger pull which cocks the hammer, and single action short crisp trigger pull on subsequent shots.  An ambidextrous safety/decocker is featured for convenience and ultimate safety especially when keeping a round chambered. The internals show little wear and have been polished for smoother action and well lubricated to preserve the aluminum alloy frame. Even with the stainless steel slide, weight is just 28.8 ozs. unloaded, perfect for concealed carry.The full 3 finger grip houses 8 round curved buttplate magazines suitable for even large hands. The pistol is shown with the cocked factory bobbed hammer many prefer for concealed carry. The grooved top makes it easy to grip for manual cocking  I'm a S&W 3rd Gen collector so I've pnly put about 250 rounds through this pistol and have had absolutely no function issues whatsoever over the year I've owned it. The 3rd Gens are well known for reliability and were popular duty weapons until phased out due to production cost.  The S&W case is new and not labeled. More pictures available upon request. Cash deal offers only - No trades. Valid driver's license must be presented. I'm willing to meet anywhere in the Tampa - St.Pete area to show this impressive pistol. Shipping to an FFL available. Send a message for more info or to request a call or text.
